{
  "page": "Shoulder-riding game",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Note:</b> The title of this article is conjecture and may be subject to change.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>shoulder-riding game</b> is a water game played by at least four people, often children, but sometimes adults. The participants form at least two pairs of people, where each pair has one person riding the shoulders of the other in a body of water.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The teams may mock-<a href=\"/index.php/Joust\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Joust\">joust</a> each other, playacting a <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horse</a> and rider. The object of the game is to knock down or separate an opposing team through team effort, making them fall into the water.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Shoulder-riding_game&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The game is often played by children in the pools of the <a href=\"/index.php/Water_Gardens\" title=\"Water Gardens\">Water Gardens</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Shoulder-riding_game&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran Martell</a> and his brother <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn</a> played the game in the Water Gardens when they were children. Doran was ten years older than Oberyn, so he had left the pools by the time his younger brother was old enough to play, but would watch him while visiting <a href=\"/index.php/Princess_of_Dorne_(mother_of_Doran)\" title=\"Princess of Dorne (mother of Doran)\">their mother</a>. Oberyn fought fiercely and quickly, often toppling boys much bigger than himself.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Martell\" title=\"Arianne Martell\">Arianne Martell</a> was a child in the Water Gardens, she used to play the game with her friends. She sometimes rode the shoulders of <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Fowler\" title=\"Jeyne Fowler\">Jeyne</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Jennelyn_Fowler\" title=\"Jennelyn Fowler\">Jennelyn Fowler</a>, or her friend <a href=\"/index.php/Frynne\" title=\"Frynne\">Frynne</a>. Her favorite steed was <a href=\"/index.php/Garin_(orphan)\" title=\"Garin (orphan)\">Garin</a>, since if she rode him, nobody could defeat them, not even <a href=\"/index.php/Nymeria_Sand\" title=\"Nymeria Sand\">Nymeria Sand</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Archon%27s_green-haired_daughter\" title=\"Archon&#39;s green-haired daughter\">Archon's green-haired daughter</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_events\">Recent events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Shoulder-riding_game&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Shoulder-riding_game&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>At the <a href=\"/index.php/Water_Gardens\" title=\"Water Gardens\">Water Gardens</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Obara_Sand\" title=\"Obara Sand\">Obara Sand</a> meets with <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran Martell</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Dorne\" title=\"Prince of Dorne\">Prince of Dorne</a>, demanding vengeance for her father, <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn Martell</a>, who was slain by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>. Doran makes Obara look at the children playing the shoulder-riding game in the pools, and while they watch, a nut-brown girl yanks a towheaded boy off his brother's shoulders, making him fall headfirst into the pool. Doran tells Obara that her father often used to defeat boys much larger than himself when he played in the pools as a child. Doran adds that before Oberyn left for King's Landing, he promised Doran he would do it again, without which Doran would not have let him go. The story does not comfort Obara.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Outside of <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> notices two washerwomen playing with <a href=\"/index.php/Raff\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Raff\">Raff</a> and another <a href=\"/index.php/Man-at-arms\" title=\"Man-at-arms\">man-at-arms</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Fork\" title=\"Red Fork\">river</a>'s shallows, with the women riding the men's shoulders and mock <a href=\"/index.php/Joust\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Joust\">jousting</a>. The girls are half-drunk and half-naked, laughing and snapping rolled-up cloaks at one another, while a dozen other men encourage them. Jaime bets a <a href=\"/index.php/Copper\" title=\"Copper\">copper</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Currency\" title=\"Currency\">star</a> on the blonde girl riding Raff, but loses it when Raff and the girl fall down in the reeds.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Prince Doran Martell tells his daughter <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Martell\" title=\"Arianne Martell\">Arianne</a> that <a href=\"/index.php/Ellaria_Sand\" title=\"Ellaria Sand\">Ellaria Sand</a> and her daughters are safe at the Water Gardens, where <a href=\"/index.php/Elia_Sand\" title=\"Elia Sand\">Elia</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Obella_Sand\" title=\"Obella Sand\">Obella Sand</a> have become \"the terror of the pools\". Doran says that it is not that long since Arianne played in the pools, and reminisces about how she would ride the shoulders of an <a href=\"/index.php/Fowler_twins\" title=\"Fowler twins\">older blonde girl</a>. When Arianne mentions she used to play with a <a href=\"/index.php/Hair_dye\" title=\"Hair dye\">green-haired</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\">Tyroshi</a> girl, Doran says that she was the <a href=\"/index.php/Archon_of_Tyrosh\" title=\"Archon of Tyrosh\">Archon's</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Archon%27s_green-haired_daughter\" title=\"Archon&#39;s green-haired daughter\">daughter</a>, and that Arianne was supposed to have been sent to Tyrosh in her place, to <a href=\"/index.php/Secret_marriage_pact\" title=\"Secret marriage pact\">secretly meet</a> with her <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys Targaryen\">betrothed</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Shoulder-riding_game&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>A score or more had gathered in the <a href=\"/index.php/Water_Gardens\" title=\"Water Gardens\">big pool</a>, to watch the battles as smaller children rode through the waist-deep shallows on the shoulders of the larger and tried to shove each other into the water. Every time a pair went down, the splash was followed by a roar of laughter.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Areo_Hotah\" title=\"Areo Hotah\">Areo Hotah</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>They splashed in the pools and fountains of the <a href=\"/index.php/Water_Gardens\" title=\"Water Gardens\">Water Gardens</a>, and rode into battle perched on one another's naked backs.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Martell\" title=\"Arianne Martell\">Arianne Martell</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>When I rode <a href=\"/index.php/Garin_(orphan)\" title=\"Garin (orphan)\">Garin</a> no one could defeat us, not even <a href=\"/index.php/Nymeria_Sand\" title=\"Nymeria Sand\">Nym</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Archon%27s_green-haired_daughter\" title=\"Archon&#39;s green-haired daughter\">that green-haired Tyroshi girl</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Martell\" title=\"Arianne Martell\">Arianne Martell</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_als